cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR. 

The paper focuses on learning syntactic representations and structures from natural images and paired captions, which falls under the intersection of computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel approach using neural networks, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on a large dataset, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
